# Snyk (https://snyk.io) policy file.
#
# Reviewed 2026-06-28: every Snyk Code (SAST) finding in the paths below was
# assessed and confirmed to be a false positive — none is a real vulnerability.
# They are excluded from Snyk Code analysis so they stop recurring. None of
# these files is part of the shipped service binary (cmd/tailscale2otel).
#
# 1. *_test.go "Use of Hardcoded Passwords" (go/HardcodedPassword/test):
#    dummy literals used as bait to prove the secret-redaction logic works.
#    Snyk tags the rule itself `/test`; they must stay literals for the tests
#    to be meaningful.
# 2. CLI build/generator tools "Path Traversal" (go/PT, python/PT): the file
#    path flows from a trusted developer/CI argument (flag.String / argparse
#    --out|--raw|--old|--new). Not network-reachable, never runs in the service.
version: v1.25.0
exclude:
  code:
    # Hardcoded-password test bait (secret-redaction tests).
    - internal/app/admin_status_test.go
    - internal/app/profiling_test.go
    - internal/config/secret_test.go
    - internal/config/validate_test.go
    # Local build/generator tools — trusted CLI path arguments.
    - internal/portservice/gen.go
    - tools/apidrift/main.go
    - tools/metricscatalog/main.go
    - deploy/alerts/gen/build_rules.py
    - deploy/grafana/gen/build.py
